  "title": "HEALTH, SAFETY AND ENVIRONMENTAL (HSE) OFFICER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u><br />Conduct regular site safety inspections.<br />Carry out incident investigations and propose corrective actions to be implemented<br />Conduct/ Review Risk Assessments<br />Implementing EHS management systems<br />Organize and conduct internal EHS trainings for staff <br />Ensure compliance with all legal and regulatory requirements<br /><br /><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u><br />Degree / Diploma in any discipline.<br />Candidate must be a registered Workplace Safety & Health Officer & ECO.<br />At least 2 years of working experience in construction industry (Preferable in LTA projects or other civil works) Experience and well verse with EHS procedures with experience in bizSAFE programme. <br />Candidates should be dynamic, self-motivated, proactive, and results oriented<br />Familiar with ISO 45001, ISO 14001, SS 506 & CP79.</p>",
